
1) Generate key pair
   ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "email@domain"

2) Add public key to Github account
   By default public key is hosted in  ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub. Copy it with vim or xclip
   xclip -sel clip ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub
   And then put it on github.

3) Add to ~/.ssh/config 
    
  Host github.com
    Hostname github.com
    User git
    IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_rsa
  
4) Copy repository with git clone 4) Copy repository with git clone 4) Copy repository with git clone 4) Copy repository with git clone 


